RACE.FOOTNOTES: STRIKE THE POSE had a good position outside tracking the speed duel upfront, waited to pounce midway on the turn, cruised to the lead outside in the four path turning for home and was kept to the task late drawing away comfortably at the wire. HUMOR ME JIM set the fractions down the backstretch on the rail, surrendered the lead at the three eighths pole running inside, was in contention at the top of the lane on the fence and determinedly battled on late besting the rest in the end. SPEEDY JOHNY was on the rail in the second flight stalking the early speed duel, was roused inside at the quarter pole, shifted out to the three path for the drive and closed in for third passing a tired runner in the late stages of the race. I'M A BOURBON GIRL hounded the pacesetter outside at the half, took command in the two path at the three furlong marker, was in between runners vying for the lead turning for home and tired in mid stretch. SANDY GRACE broke with the field but soon dropped back outside to trail, was hustled for more to keep pace with the other rivals down the backside, could not get into contention on the turn and was never a factor in the lane. PER RULING FROM THE ONTARIO RACING COMMISSION, SANDY GRACE WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR CARRYING TOO LITTLE WEIGHT.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIT AND RUN was reined back at the half watching the contesting trio battle up front, waited inside midway on the turn to offer a run, shifted outwards to the four path for the drive and wore down the leaders in the stretch to get up for the win. ANITA GRIGIO hounded the frontrunner outside in the early going, bid for the lead three furlongs from the prize, had a short lead between horses as they straightened out for the drive and stubbornly gave way to the winner a hundred yards from the line. GORMLEY GIRL broke out, bumping foe at the start, advanced smartly up the rail three eighths from the finish, was in range behind horses in the three path in upper stretch and split runners late to close in and capture third. MISS BOBBIT was unhurried early trailing the field down the backstretch, began to unleash her run midpoint on the turn three wide around challengers, was six wide at the top of the lane and was closing in for a share while on the wrong lead to the wire. WEST PAW broke inwards to start bumping a rival, settled near the back outside in the beginning, could not gain on other runners through the turn and could only offer an even finish running down the stretch. J M R BOLD VISION pressed the issue on the rail down the backstretch, took the lead inside entering the turn, fought gamely on the rail turning for home and faded on the fence in deep stretch. WAKE UP MAGGIE stalked in mid pack outside with four furlongs remaining, made little impression running on the turn and was not involved in the stretch drive. TAKE IT EASY had a short lead with runners on either side at the half, began to give way between foes three furlongs from home, backed away through the field at the quarter pole and galloped to the wire.

DON'T STOP DREAMIN settled at the back on the rail down the backside, was on hold in tight quarters inside on the turn, steadied at the three eighths pole then midpoint on the turn and could not recover to play a role down the lane.
